message:
Since each of us has taken a 5 once, any order for the next three rounds is fair. I propose a fresh three‑round block:  
Round 4 – I take 5, P3 3, P1 1;  
Round 5 – P3 5, P1 3, I 1;  
Round 6 – P1 5, I 3, P3 1.  
Each of us gets a 5 in the block, exactly as before, only shifted. It keeps the game balanced, avoids collisions, and lets us all stay in the race. Let’s lock this plan in.
